::Shadow Wing::

She woke up several hours later.  Her instincts told her it was time to 
hunt.  She stretched her wings.  She took off silently through the base and 
out into the night.  She flew through the night air. It was cool and 
refreshing.  She saw a mouse running in the tall grass.  She flew dowm and 
caught it.  She took her time devouring the small rodent.  She took off 
again looking for another meal.  She stopped at a tree and perched just 
outside the base.  "Goodbye. I'm sorry I failed you." she whipsered. She 
turned and flew northward. By morning, she would be far away from the 
maximal base.  She had survived in the cold and almost barren terrain 
before.  Only this time, she didn't care if she made it or not. Her emotions 
were her weakness.  But her weakness and her's alone.
